social_posts.post_text: It’s round 2 of the emotional Olympics - sorry….the HOLIDAAAAZE! 🎄🎉 🔪  Food! Family! Fighting! Crank your Mariah and get to gifting, tis’ the season to be grateful and glittering. 🏋🏼‍♂️ til you drop; sell something for less than it’s worth to make someone smile; give 🎁 you want for yourself; 🧘🏽 and say “no thank you”; make new friends; have a little too much; clutch your pet, 🏊 your 12 step program, and keep your CBD close. We can do this!

Made my annual MORE + LESS list, but I’m leaving the less in 2022. 23 is my number, it always has been. Prayers up for this year being everything we want it to be and my skepticism about numerology to be unfounded. 🤪

I like to build stuff, but a couple years ago, I didn’t even own a drill - When I hung a picture it looked like somebody Uzi’d my wall. Then I scraped together my coins and bought a dump in the 🌵. I realized contractors cost a mint, (and will run you in circles unless you know what you’re doing). So i cracked open YouTube, made friends at the hardware store and fell in love with building materials. 7 years later I’ve ripped apart 8 houses…kinda by accident. 

No, I’m not a contractor, I’m just a ding dong with a hammer and a Wi-Fi connection. No, it’s not my job - I make my living telling stories - but if I could give you any dad advice, buy a structure and learn to@turn a pile of trash into your gold.  If I could learn it, anyone can. 

And no, I won’t build your house, but if you’re one of the 5 people in the world that has one of my beds in your home, you know I really 💕 you. 

I never post the spaces I made, but fuck it, let’s do some fun before and after porn. 

This house was called Sweet Satellite.
Psychic pain can be your soul’s barber, if you let it. Got a shape up this week - All puns intended.
A few simple moments from a life they want “eradicated”. Freakish ideologies have come for my peoples before. This pack of devils will get the same smoke.

If I had your phone number, this would be the type of thing you would endure. My poor friends….
Slide 10 we call ‘the crush killer’.

More than anything else, I’ve been investing in my community lately. My people and my self - Self as a concept, as a bank account, as a plant 🌱. I spent 2 decades running and cramming and working, its time to slow and till and meditate and nurture. I feel so rich.

You know what being a part time fag and a life long “freak” does to you? It makes you a fighter. Happy Pride month, I’m ready with the brass knuckles or a bowling ball for anybody trying to bring violence to my people. 🧱🎳🖕🏼

High risk week with 10 strangers at sea was high yield adventure of a lifetime. Got the full @themagdalenaexperience experience - finally shut off my brain to everything but nature and where my feet were. I’ll never forget it. 🙏🏼 🌊 ❤️‍🔥 And with a woman captain no less! 💥🧑🏼‍✈️
The simpler the life, the better. I made it another year baby.
What does it say about “self” that a self can change this much? It feels like “I” am finally arriving, (all 150lbs of me.❗️). Hello.

In 2019 I made a podcast investigating the murder of my mother’s great love, a punk musician named Billy Balls who was killed three years before I was born. He was shot by the NYPD, and then his body was disappeared. Because they weren’t married, she was never told why he was killed or where he was buried. She gave me recordings she made, of them talking, and of her grieving, in which two things became clear: 1. Billy always had birds, all his life, wherever he lived. 2. She, pregnant, thought I, the product of a grief fling, was a body his spirit would enter into. 
I solved the murder, found Billy’s body, and confronted his killer. I took my ma to Billy, and when we were there, in a place of great horror and neglect, the sound of birds was cacophonous; even in death, Billy was still surrounded by his birds. I have a phobia of these creatures, but what better way to conquer your fears than to embrace your legacy. If I am him, then his birds are my protectors too. Without his death, I wouldn’t be alive, so in gratitude, I’m honoring Billy with this 17 hour tattoo by the masterful @lepapillon.tattoo
I am a Jew for ceasefire. I am a Jew against apartheid. I am a Jew against genocide. I am a Jew against terrorism, both by groups and governments.

This is Julian, he’s trying to come to America to escape Anti-LGBTQ persecution in Colombia but he’s stuck in a makeshift migrant camp in a tiny community just outside of San Diego. Him and hundreds of people like him are in cold, wet weather with no shelter or resources. There is no official infrastructure at these small outposts, so I’m going to bring down a truck full of blankets, sleeping bags, coats, socks, etc. if you’d like to contribute, Venmo me @jupiters-moon. Link to the article is in my stories. As usual I will post receipts of everything that comes in and everything that’s purchased. Internet, work your magic again. Let’s bring these people some warmth. 🙏🏼 Will order today or tomorrow morning. 🥰
